- packages: WinUI, EntityFrameworkCore, BCrypt.Net

---

## versions
- WinUI: 3
- C#: 12
- .NET: 8
- MySQL: 8

---

## code style
- models: PascalCase
- classnames: PascalCase
- methods: PascalCase
- properties: PascalCase
- private variables: _camelCase
- constants: UPPER_CASE

Example


public class ProductService
{
private readonly AppDbContext _db;

public void LoadProducts()
{
}

}


---

## folders & files

- models in `Data`
- validations in `Data/Validation`
- Pages in `Pages`
- business logic in `Services`
- helper functions in `Helpers`

Example structure


/Data
/Data/Models
/Data/Validation

/Pages
/Pages/Product
/Pages/User

/Services

/Helpers

/Assets


---

## CRUD Functions

Every entity should support basic CRUD functionality.

Standard pages

- OverviewPage
- CreatePage
- DetailPage
- EditPage

Naming example


ProductOverviewPage.xaml
ProductCreatePage.xaml
ProductEditPage.xaml
ProductDetailPage.xaml


Database tables

- tablenames: PascalCase
- primary key: Id

Example


User
Product
Order
OrderProduct


---

## validation

- validations belong in the ViewModel
- use DataConverters for simple format checks
- avoid validation inside UI code

Examples


number validation
date validation
string length validation


---

## database

- database engine: MySQL
- version: 8.0

Entity rules

- every table has an `Id`
- foreign keys must be explicit
- navigation properties should be defined
- DbContext name must be `AppDbContext`

Example


public DbSet<User> Users { get; set; }
public DbSet<Product> Products { get; set; }


---

## file- and mapstructure


/Pages
/Data
/Services
/Helpers
/Assets
/Views


Explanation

- `/Pages` → only XAML pages
- `/Data` → models, DbContext and validation
- `/Services` → API calls, datastore logic, calculations
- `/Helpers` → utility classes
- `/Assets` → images, icons, fonts
- `/Views` → reusable UI components

---

## XAML template

Use strong binding.

Example

<TextBlock Text="{x:Bind Product.Name}" /> ```

Rules

prefer {x:Bind} instead of {Binding}
use reusable UI components
application theme: darkmode
commands

Commands must be used instead of click-events.

Not allowed

<Button Click="Button_Click"/>

Allowed

<Button Command="{x:Bind SaveCommand}"/>

Commands may be named in Dutch if required.

Layouts (Reusable UI)

Reusable UI components must be stored in

/Views/Layouts

Naming rule

HeaderLayout.xaml
FooterLayout.xaml
DashboardLayout.xaml

Layouts should contain

navigation
headers
shared UI blocks
authentication

Use BCrypt for password hashing.

Example

string hash = BCrypt.Net.BCrypt.HashPassword(password);

Verify password

BCrypt.Net.BCrypt.Verify(password, user.PasswordHash);

Never store plain passwords.

notifications

Use WinUI components for notifications.

Allowed

InfoBar
ContentDialog
AppNotification

Example

MyInfoBar.Title = "Success";
MyInfoBar.Message = "Product saved";
MyInfoBar.IsOpen = true;
error handling

Always check for null values.

Example

var user = db.Users.FirstOrDefault();

if (user == null)
{
    return;
}

Use safe parsing.

double.TryParse(value, out double result)
architecture overview
Pages (UI)

↓

Services (Logic)

↓

Data (DbContext + Models)

↓

Database

This structure keeps the application maintainable and scalable.


