### 🧭 WinUI Project Conventions

# Project conventions

## General guidelines
- Always use WinUI built-in structures
- All code must be written in english
- Avoid business logic inside XAML code-behind
- Keep UI, logic and data separated
- Prefer reusable components instead of duplicated UI
- Always use descriptive names for variables, classes and pages
- Avoid magic numbers or hardcoded values in code
- Keep methods small and readable
- Always check for null values before accessing objects

---

