## CRUD Functions

Each entity must support CRUD operations.

Standard pages

- OverviewPage
- CreatePage
- DetailPage
- EditPage

Example


ProductOverviewPage.xaml
ProductCreatePage.xaml
ProductDetailPage.xaml
ProductEditPage.xaml


CRUD operations

- Create
- Read
- Update
- Delete

Example


db.Products.Add(product)
db.Products.Remove(product)
db.SaveChanges()


---

## validation
- validations belong in the ViewModel
- never validate directly inside XAML
- use DataConverters for simple format checks
- use validation attributes where possible

Examples


number validation
date validation
required fields
string length validation


Example


if(string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(NameTextBox.Text))
{
return;
}


---

## database
- database engine: MySQL
- version: 8.0

Entity rules

- every table must have an `Id`
- relationships must use foreign keys
- navigation properties should always be defined
- DbContext name must be `AppDbContext`
- DbSet names must be plural

Example


public DbSet<User> Users { get; set; }
public DbSet<Product> Products { get; set; }
public DbSet<Order> Orders { get; set; }


---

## Entity rules

Entities must only contain:

- properties
- navigation properties
- simple calculated fields

Avoid

- database queries
- service logic
- API calls

Example


public double TotalPrice => OrderProducts.Sum(p => p.Product.Price);


---

## file- and mapstructure


/Pages
/Data
/Services
/Helpers
/Views
/Assets


Explanation

- `/Pages` → only XAML pages
- `/Data` → models, DbContext and validation
- `/Services` → API calls, datastore logic, calculations
- `/Helpers` → utility classes
- `/Views` → reusable UI components
- `/Assets` → images, icons and fonts

---

## XAML template

Use strong binding.

Example

<TextBlock Text="{x:Bind Product.Name}" /> ```

Rules

prefer {x:Bind} instead of {Binding}
use x:DataType for compile-time checking
avoid inline logic in XAML
application theme: darkmode

Example

<DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Product">
commands

Commands should be used instead of click-events where possible.

Not allowed

<Button Click="Button_Click"/>

Allowed

<Button Command="{x:Bind SaveCommand}"/>

Commands may be named in Dutch if required.

Layouts (Reusable UI)

Reusable UI components must be stored in

/Views/Layouts

Naming rule

HeaderLayout.xaml
FooterLayout.xaml
DashboardLayout.xaml
NavigationLayout.xaml

Layouts should contain

navigation
headers
shared UI components
reusable page structures
authentication

Use BCrypt for password hashing.

Example

string hash = BCrypt.Net.BCrypt.HashPassword(password);

Verify password

BCrypt.Net.BCrypt.Verify(password, user.PasswordHash);

Rules

never store plain passwords
always store hashed passwords
password property name must be
PasswordHash
notifications

Use WinUI components for notifications.

Allowed components

InfoBar
ContentDialog

Example

MyInfoBar.Title = "Success";
MyInfoBar.Message = "Product saved";
MyInfoBar.IsOpen = true;
error handling

Always check for null values.

Example

var user = db.Users.FirstOrDefault();

if(user == null)
{
    return;
}

Use safe parsing.

double.TryParse(value, out double result)